Tracks the hourly count of unique source IP addresses communicating with specified external IP ranges and hosts, helping identify spikes in network activity, scanning, or potential threat actor infrastructure interactions.

Detailed Description

This Splunk search analyzes network traffic in the chick index by:

Monitoring communications involving:
185.186.244.0/24
172.94.9.0/24
185.93.89.37
185.93.89.138
Matching traffic where either:
The source IP falls within the monitored infrastructure, or
The destination IP falls within the monitored infrastructure.
Calculating the number of distinct source IP addresses (dc(src)).
Aggregating results into 1-hour intervals using timechart.
Producing a trend line showing unique source IP activity over time.
Security Use Cases
Threat hunting for known malicious infrastructure
Monitoring communications with suspicious IP ranges
Detecting scanning or reconnaissance activity
Measuring exposure to threat actor infrastructure
Identifying sudden increases in external connections
Investigating command-and-control (C2) communications
Tracking campaign activity over time


index=*addindex*
(
    (src>= "185.186.244.0" AND src<= "185.186.244.255")
    OR (dst>= "185.186.244.0" AND dst<= "185.186.244.255")
    OR (src>= "172.94.9.0" AND src<= "172.94.9.255")
    OR (dst>= "172.94.9.0" AND dst<= "172.94.9.255")
    OR src="185.93.89.37" 
    OR dst="185.93.89.37"
    OR src="185.93.89.138" 
    OR dst="185.93.89.138"
    )
| timechart span=1h dc(src) AS unique_source_ips
